<COREF ID="11" TYPE="IDENT">The bridge loans</COREF> are intended to provide temporary financing for acquisitions .
Since such loans are often refinanced through the sale of high - risk , high - yield junk bonds , the recent woes of the junk - bond market have renewed concerns among regulators about the risks associated with <COREF ID="9" TYPE="IDENT">Wall Street</COREF> firms issuing bridge loans .
